    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` namespace\n\n### What I found\n\nThe codebase already has all the pieces needed:\n- A fully-featured INI parser at **`src/ini.zig`** (the `Parser` struct), already accessible via `bun.ini`\n- A consistent 6-file wiring pattern used by `Bun.TOML`, `Bun.YAML`, `Bun.JSONC`, and `Bun.JSON5`\n\n### Files to touch (7 total)\n\n| # | File | Change |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` | **New** — `create()`, `parse()`, `stringify()` |\n| 2 | `src/bun.js/api.zig` | Add `pub const INIObject = ...` import |\n| 3 | `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | Add lazy callback, export, and getter function |\n| 4 | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | Add `INI` row to `@begin bunObjectTable` LUT |\n| 5 | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | Add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER` |\n| 6 | `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | Add `namespace INI { parse, stringify }` |\n| 7 | `test/js/bun/ini/ini-public-api.test.ts` | **New** — end-to-end tests |\n\n### Key design decisions\n- **`parse`**: Reuses `bun.ini.Parser` directly (same parser used for `.npmrc`); uses `globalThis.bunVM().transpiler.env` for env var handling (consistent with the internal test API)\n- **`stringify`**: Implemented from scratch — scalars first as `key = value`, then objects as `[section]` blocks, nested objects become dotted headers (`[a.b.c]`), arrays as repeated `key[] = value` lines\n- No new interchange module needed — `src/ini.zig` is referenced directly",
